•	
7.1.1 - W11SR05: Insufficient Endpoint Application Control
ISM controls:
•	0041; 0043; 1657 (Relating to the implementation and enforcement of application control).
•	0329; 0330 (Relating to the restriction of administrative privileges and local administrator accounts).
•	1416 (Relating to the validation of software integrity and application execution).
Current Risk There is a risk that insufficient or ineffective implementation of endpoint application control and protection measures (specifically regarding the use of AirLocker or AppLocker for stand-alone workstations) could allow the execution of unapproved or malicious software. This may lead to a loss of data integrity, the exposure or exfiltration of sensitive information, or a significant loss of system availability across the Windows 11 fleet.
Risk Assessment:
Risk Likelihood	x	Risk Consequence	=	Risk Rating
LIKELY	x	MODERATE	=	HIGH
Recommendations:
•	Mandatory Application Control Policy: Enforce a strict "Allow list" policy for all executable files, scripts, and installers on stand-alone workstations, ensuring only approved departmental software can run.
•	Integrate with Intune/Endpoint Manager: Centralise the management of application control policies to ensure consistent enforcement and rapid deployment of updates across both networked and stand-alone devices.
•	Removal of Local Administrative Rights: Ensure all users operate with standard user privileges to prevent the manual bypass of application control mechanisms and reduce the potential impact of malware.
- Treatment #1
•	Implement AirLocker/AppLocker in "Enforce" mode with digital signature validation for all mission-critical applications.
•	Conduct regular audits of application execution logs via a centralised SIEM or local log collector to identify attempted executions of unauthorised software.
•	Establish a formalised process for the rapid assessment and "Allow listing" of new software requirements to prevent user circumvention of security controls.
Residual risk outcome if recommendation is implemented. The implementation of robust application control and the removal of local administrative rights significantly reduces the attack surface of the Windows 11 environment. By ensuring that only verified, signed, and approved applications can execute, the likelihood of a malware-based incident is reduced to "Unlikely." While the consequence of a compromise remains "Moderate," the overall risk is brought within the agency's acceptable threshold.
Risk Likelihood	x	Risk Consequence	=	Risk Rating
UNLIKELY	x	MODERATE	=	MEDIUM

